    "A change is randomly selected according to the proposal distribution and then accepted or not using a stochastic acceptance condition.",
    "The proposal distribution and acceptance condition are chosen so that models with high posterior probabilities are preferred.",
    "Provided certain conditions are met, the states generated by the Markov chain stabilise to a stationary distribution of models which represents a sample of the true posterior distribution.",
    "These conditions include that the chain must be irreducible such that every model is reachable from every other model in a finite number of steps.",
    "Madigan et al. (1995) used MH to sample DAGs in the MC 3 algorithm."
